## ✅ Code Review Checklist

### Architecture
- [ ] No circular dependencies
- [ ] Dependency direction respected (Presentation → Domain → Data)
- [ ] No direct imports between features
- [ ] All data layer behind interfaces

### Code Quality
- [ ] No TODOs or FIXMEs (or documented why)
- [ ] No magic numbers (use constants)
- [ ] No dead code
- [ ] Functions are focused (single responsibility)
- [ ] Error handling is comprehensive

### Kotlin Standards
- [ ] Immutability preferred (val, sealed, PersistentList)
- [ ] Null safety observed (?.let, elvis, no !!)
- [ ] No println() or Log (use logging framework)
- [ ] String templates used (not concatenation)
- [ ] Naming follows conventions

### Compose Standards
- [ ] Screen/View pattern respected
- [ ] Error flow uses `UiError` (not raw `Exception`), `error.message` in snackbar (not `.toString()`)
- [ ] Lifecycle triggers use `OnLifecycleEventEffect` (not raw `DisposableEffect + LifecycleEventObserver`)
- [ ] Recomposition — Tier 1 (always apply, negligible complexity cost):
  - [ ] All `UiState` sealed classes annotated with `@Immutable`
  - [ ] All UI model `data class` annotated with `@Immutable` (or `@Stable` if they contain `Uri` or other non-annotated-but-reliable types)
  - [ ] All collection fields in UI models use `PersistentList<>`, not `List<>`
  - [ ] Lambda parameters consumed inside `observeWithLifecycle` protected with `rememberUpdatedState`
  - [ ] All lazy `items { }` use `key = { it.id }`
  - [ ] All single `item { }` blocks in lazy layouts have a string key: `item(key = "header") { ... }`
  - [ ] All `SharedFlow` collected via `observeWithLifecycle()` from coreui (lifecycle-aware)
  - [ ] Values derived from parameters (sumOf, filter, count…) wrapped in `remember(param) { ... }`
- [ ] Recomposition — Tier 2 (only on screens with LazyList / LazyGrid / animations):
  - [ ] Navigation lambdas capturing `context`/`viewModel` wrapped in `remember(viewModel, context) { ... }`
  - [ ] Leaf composables (cards, list items) receive only the fields they actually display — not the full model object
  - [ ] Per-item lambdas inside lazy item lambdas use `remember(item.id, callback) { { callback(item.id) } }`
  - Note: `DashboardScreen`, `SearchFriendScreen`, `MyFriendListScreen`, `MyFriendDetailScreen`, `MyProfileScreen` are Tier 2 screens in this project
- [ ] No lazy layout (`LazyColumn`, `LazyVerticalGrid`…) nested inside a scrollable container (`Column + verticalScroll`, `Row + horizontalScroll`)
- [ ] View derives all displayed data from `uiState` — no duplicate parameters that also exist in the state (single source of truth)
- [ ] Navigation routes carry only IDs — not display data (`name`, `description`, `imageUrl`)
- [ ] Preview composables for all states
- [ ] Wrapped in PokeManiacTheme
- [ ] Proper lambda passing (trailing syntax)

### Coroutines
- [ ] viewModelScope used (not GlobalScope)
- [ ] Flow collection proper (collectLatest, collect)
- [ ] Error handling with try/catch — `CancellationException` always rethrown, others emit `UiError.from(e)`
- [ ] No blocking operations
- [ ] Proper dispatcher selection

### Testing
- [ ] Tests follow Given/When/Then
- [ ] Mocks used appropriately
- [ ] Edge cases tested
- [ ] Error scenarios tested
- [ ] Tests are deterministic (no flakiness)

### Git/Commits
- [ ] Commits are atomic and logical
- [ ] Commit messages are descriptive
- [ ] No merge conflicts
- [ ] No credentials in code
- [ ] No unnecessary files committed

